Hi <@U03TNH9A1CJ>
I had a more senior dev solve this years ago and only up to a point. The only issue It had was the transparency kept going away. And I am not sure that can be fixed because it is something that Safari is not very supportive of. But the video should play. Here is the code block of the module where the video file would be placed:
```{% if module.video.videourl.url.type == 'FILE' %}
	&lt;video &gt;
		{% set names = module.video.videourl.url.href|split('webm', 2) %}
		{% for name in names %}
		    {% if loop.index ==1 %} 
				&lt;source src="{{name}}mov" type='video/mp4; codecs="hvc1"'&gt;
			{% endif %}
		{% endfor %}
				&lt;source src="{{module.video.videourl.url.href}}" type="video/webm"&gt;
	&lt;/video&gt;  
{% endif %}```
And it is important to upload the two videos into the file manager with the exact same name with the only difference between the two being the extension (.webm and .mp4)

Hope this makes sense
